WEBVTT

00:05:27.203 --> 00:05:33.263
This is what white sociologist
Robin DiAngelo calls "white fragility."

00:05:33.287 --> 00:05:35.084
She argues that, in fact,

00:05:35.108 --> 00:05:39.147
because whites have
so little experience being challenged

00:05:39.171 --> 00:05:40.644
about their white privilege

00:05:40.668 --> 00:05:44.163
that whenever even the most
minute challenge is brought before them,

00:05:44.187 --> 00:05:46.010
they usually cry,

00:05:46.034 --> 00:05:47.185
get angry

00:05:47.209 --> 00:05:48.360
or run.

00:05:48.384 --> 00:05:49.389
(Laughter)

00:05:49.413 --> 00:05:52.400
And I have experienced them all.

00:05:52.424 --> 00:05:58.236
And so, when I was contemplating
confronting his teacher,

00:05:58.260 --> 00:05:59.833
I wasn't happy about it,

00:05:59.857 --> 00:06:01.920
but I was like, this is a necessary evil